WEBVTT

01:40.600 --> 01:42.976
- Looks just as good.
- Where do you get these?

01:43.144 --> 01:45.229
- He's got a million.
- They're so funny.

01:45.396 --> 01:48.357
Just remember,
don't mention the Communists.

01:48.525 --> 01:50.567
Calvin's a great guy,
but he's a little....

01:50.735 --> 01:52.569
- Nutty?
- What's his wife like?

01:52.737 --> 01:55.697
- You know, housewife.
- Likes to cook.

01:55.865 --> 01:57.866
- Pregnant.
- Normal, then.

01:58.076 --> 01:59.910
I wouldn't go that far.

02:00.078 --> 02:01.620
- Helen. Hi.
- Oh, hi, Betty.

02:01.788 --> 02:04.581
- Hi, Dave.
- Just look at you.

02:04.749 --> 02:07.084
- Any day now.
- Say hi to my sister, Ruth...

02:07.252 --> 02:09.377
Tell me if you heard this one.

02:09.545 --> 02:12.089
- A duck walks into a drugstore.
- Ha, ha.

02:12.257 --> 02:14.758
He says, "I'd like some lip gloss."

02:14.926 --> 02:17.928
The clerk says, "Certainly, sir.
Will this be cash or check?"

02:18.096 --> 02:21.849
- The duck says, "Put it on my bill." Ah?
- Ha-ha-ha.

02:24.144 --> 02:25.269
Oh, brother.

02:25.436 --> 02:28.397
He was a golden-boy professor
at Caltech.

02:28.565 --> 02:30.315
But then he started inventing things.

02:30.567 --> 02:35.821
He suddenly became very rich,
and that was it, he quit teaching.

02:36.030 --> 02:39.825
- How's that?
- Just what the doctor ordered. Ha, ha!

02:39.993 --> 02:45.122
Calvin spends all of his time out there,
tinkering around in the workshop.

02:45.290 --> 02:47.624
If you ask me, it's all very strange.

02:47.792 --> 02:49.126
Same is true of batteries.

02:49.335 --> 02:54.965
I could take your simple yacht battery
and rig it to last a decade, easily.

02:55.592 --> 02:56.633
Say, Helen...

02:56.801 --> 02:59.636
what does Calvin think
about this trouble down in Cuba?

02:59.804 --> 03:03.432
Oh, for heaven's sakes,
please don't bring that up.

03:12.650 --> 03:17.446
I'd say my baseball card collection
is as complete as any one I've ever seen.

03:17.614 --> 03:20.115
Calvin? Hey, Calvin, Calvin.

03:20.283 --> 03:23.994
Kennedy is going toe to toe
with Khrushchev on television right now.

03:24.162 --> 03:26.663
- What?
- Ooh, boy.

03:26.873 --> 03:28.457
On the island of Cuba...

03:28.666 --> 03:31.835
unmistakable evidence
has established the fact...

03:32.003 --> 03:35.297
that a series
of offensive missile sites...

03:35.465 --> 03:39.593
is now in preparation
on that imprisoned island.

03:56.194 --> 03:59.529
Tower, this is Wolf 1.
I got five miles to the overhead.

03:59.697 --> 04:01.823
Wolf 1, Tower, report the numbers.

04:01.991 --> 04:03.492
You're number one for the overhead.

04:06.704 --> 04:09.039
Tower, this is Wolf 1,
I got a problem here.

04:09.207 --> 04:12.251
State your problem, Wolf 1.
Are you declaring an emergency?

04:12.418 --> 04:14.336
Stand by, 1.

04:14.879 --> 04:17.339
Additional sites appear
to be designed...

04:17.507 --> 04:19.507
for intermediate-range
ballistic missiles...

04:19.676 --> 04:23.053
and thus capable of striking
most of the major cities...

04:23.221 --> 04:25.389
in the western hemisphere.

04:25.556 --> 04:30.227
Folks, given this extraordinary turn
of events...

04:30.395 --> 04:33.021
I think it's prudent
we cut this evening short.

04:33.189 --> 04:35.440
I'm sure this Cuban thing
will resolve itself...

04:35.650 --> 04:36.858
but in the meantime...

04:37.026 --> 04:40.696
I suggest we take
a prayerful watch-and-wait stance.

04:42.532 --> 04:44.241
Okay, folks, let's go.

04:44.450 --> 04:46.702
Bye, Helen.
Wish it could have been longer.

04:46.869 --> 04:48.453
- My coat.
- Oh, here you go.

04:48.663 --> 04:50.789
I'll call you, Betty.

04:54.168 --> 04:55.210
What did I tell you?

04:56.587 --> 04:57.754
Thank you.

05:01.301 --> 05:03.427
I'm not gonna let this pot roast
go to waste.

05:03.594 --> 05:06.972
Calvin, could you put that seat cushion
back on the lawn chair, honey?

05:07.181 --> 05:09.308
Shouldn't we at least
turn off the phonograph?

05:09.475 --> 05:12.269
- It shuts off automatically.
- Oh. Did you rig it to do that?

05:12.437 --> 05:14.438
- They all do.
- Oh.

05:14.605 --> 05:16.273
I never know anymore.

05:18.234 --> 05:22.612
I'll bet that's a fighter jet
on its way to Key West.

05:22.780 --> 05:24.114
Good luck, amigo.

05:24.324 --> 05:26.158
An emergency has been declared.

05:26.326 --> 05:27.909
An emergency has been declared.

05:28.077 --> 05:32.289
You hear that?
I'll come back for the radio.

05:32.457 --> 05:35.459
Oh, Calvin, I wish you would've
at least let me do the dishes.

05:35.626 --> 05:39.129
It's not gonna be easy to get
all this dried-on food off my nice plates.

05:39.297 --> 05:41.965
I just hope those plates
are not radioactive by tomorrow.

05:42.133 --> 05:44.593
Well, cheese
is particularly troublesome.

05:44.802 --> 05:46.803
I've got secondaries of an engine fire.

05:46.971 --> 05:49.431
I'm gonna need to find a clear area
to eject.

05:49.599 --> 05:52.976
Roger, Wolf 1.
Can you make it to the ocean?

05:54.979 --> 05:56.730
Roger that, Tower.

05:56.939 --> 06:03.153
I'm marking the 180 radial for five
and ejecting, Tower.

06:03.321 --> 06:04.738
Roger, Wolf 1.

06:17.543 --> 06:20.504
So how long will we
have to stay down here?

06:20.671 --> 06:23.340
For this thing to blow over
could take days.

06:23.508 --> 06:26.093
Days? Honey, what if I go into labor?

06:26.260 --> 06:28.303
That could happen any time now.

06:28.471 --> 06:29.513
I've read up on it.

06:29.680 --> 06:33.475
If I have to,
I'll deliver the baby myself.

06:59.502 --> 07:01.711
Home, sweet home.

07:01.879 --> 07:03.171
To you, maybe.

07:15.017 --> 07:18.562
- Are you all right?
- I think so.

07:21.065 --> 07:25.402
Aah! It's happened.
Aah, look at that heat.

07:25.570 --> 07:30.198
All my surface indicators knocked out.
Oh, Lord!

07:30.366 --> 07:31.908
It's happened.

07:38.833 --> 07:40.125
What was that noise?

07:42.837 --> 07:44.045
The locks.

07:45.047 --> 07:46.631
The locks?

07:48.926 --> 07:52.429
To keep us from trying to leave.

07:52.597 --> 07:56.475
There's a radiation half-life
after an atomic blast.

07:56.642 --> 07:58.101
It lasts 35 years.

07:59.228 --> 08:00.937
Thirty-five years?

08:01.564 --> 08:05.984
Then, after that, it's safe to go up.

08:09.280 --> 08:13.783
According to Caltech, this Webber guy
was a bona fide genius...

08:13.951 --> 08:15.619
but a borderline nutcase.

08:15.786 --> 08:19.748
Well, he and Mrs. Nutcase must have
been out here when the plane hit.

08:19.916 --> 08:22.667
Unless we get a postcard or something,
that'd be my guess.

08:22.877 --> 08:26.296
- What about relatives?
- They're all back east.

08:26.464 --> 08:29.966
Neighbors over there said
the guy spent day and night out here.

08:30.134 --> 08:34.471
She'd bring him sandwiches
and hot Dr Pepper.

08:35.806 --> 08:38.975
- He drank it hot?
- Yeah.

08:39.477 --> 08:41.520
Good God.

08:59.664 --> 09:01.957
Hi, hon. Feeling better?

09:02.124 --> 09:03.458
No.

09:03.626 --> 09:05.252
We have to be strong...

09:05.419 --> 09:09.214
if not for ourselves, for the child.

09:13.844 --> 09:15.345
All our friends....

09:15.513 --> 09:17.681
Burnt to a crisp.

09:19.433 --> 09:22.727
- I'm not hungry.
- Hot Dr Pepper. Your favorite.

09:22.895 --> 09:25.814
No, Calvin, your favorite.

09:27.191 --> 09:28.567
Really?

09:31.737 --> 09:34.573
Chilly? Shouldn't be.

09:34.740 --> 09:38.243
- Temperature's a nice 73 degrees.
- Oh, maybe I've just got the creeps.

09:38.411 --> 09:40.787
How could you? This is just like home.

09:40.997 --> 09:43.873
No. No, Calvin.

09:44.041 --> 09:46.585
This is different, believe me.

09:46.794 --> 09:48.420
Would you like a tranquilizer?

09:49.797 --> 09:54.301
- You've got tranquilizers?
- I told you, I have everything.

09:56.304 --> 09:57.846
- What?
- Oh.

09:58.639 --> 10:00.473
Oh, hon.

10:02.351 --> 10:05.312
It's gonna be all right.
Yeah. Just breathe.

10:06.439 --> 10:08.481
I'll get my stuff.

10:11.902 --> 10:15.363
Oh, it's a good day
For singin' a song

10:15.531 --> 10:18.658
And it's a good day
For movin' along

10:18.826 --> 10:22.579
Yes, it's a good day
How could anything go wrong?

10:22.747 --> 10:25.248
A good day
From mornin' till night

10:25.416 --> 10:27.417
- Yes it's a good day
- It's a lovely day

10:27.585 --> 10:28.668
For shinin' your shoes

10:28.836 --> 10:31.087
- And it's a good day
- If you want a silver linin'

10:31.255 --> 10:32.297
For losin' the blues

10:32.465 --> 10:34.591
Everything to gain
And nothing to lose

10:36.135 --> 10:37.969
'Cause it's a good day
From mornin' to night

10:38.137 --> 10:39.179
You're right!

10:39.347 --> 10:42.849
I said to the sun "Good mornin', sun!"

10:43.017 --> 10:46.311
- Is there a problem?
- No, Calvin, babies cry.

10:47.271 --> 10:49.856
- I've noticed.
- What should we call him?

10:50.650 --> 10:51.858
I don't know.

10:52.026 --> 10:54.861
Well, I was thinking
in light of the situation...

10:55.029 --> 10:56.905
we should call him Adam.

10:57.073 --> 11:01.034
- That's not sacrilegious, is it?
- No, I think it's just right.

11:02.286 --> 11:05.622
And I was wondering if.... If....

11:06.957 --> 11:09.167
Whatever you want, Helen.

11:09.335 --> 11:10.794
I want a bedroom ceiling.

11:14.924 --> 11:16.341
You got it.

11:19.136 --> 11:22.305
'Cause it's a good day
For payin' your bills

11:22.473 --> 11:25.600
And it's a good day
For curin' your ills

11:25.768 --> 11:29.062
So take a deep breath
Throw away all your pills

11:29.230 --> 11:31.523
'Cause it's a good day
From mornin' till night

11:31.691 --> 11:34.567
See, I flick this switch...

11:34.735 --> 11:38.071
and the image is projected
onto a mirror...

11:38.239 --> 11:41.324
and the picture comes out here,
and it's perfect.

11:50.793 --> 11:53.461
- Well, almost perfect.
- Jackie Gleason.

11:53.629 --> 11:58.007
You know something? People will
never get tired of watching these.

12:07.852 --> 12:08.852
Lord...

12:09.019 --> 12:12.188
bless this food, this family...

12:12.398 --> 12:15.024
and make us ever mindful
of the needs of others.

12:15.192 --> 12:18.027
- Amen.
- Amen.

12:18.446 --> 12:19.821
Let's eat.

12:36.422 --> 12:37.797
Calvin?

12:38.466 --> 12:42.218
- Out here, hon.
- Oh, there you are.

12:42.720 --> 12:45.346
We've looked all over for you.

12:46.724 --> 12:48.767
What are you doing back here?

12:48.934 --> 12:52.395
- I was just examining this rear hatchway.
- Why?

12:54.440 --> 12:58.401
Well, it's pretty clear that when the bomb
went off, the front entrance caved in...

12:58.569 --> 13:02.655
so, you know, we'll have to return
to the surface using this back entrance...

13:02.823 --> 13:05.658
which is very nice
because it has the service elevator.

13:06.702 --> 13:10.455
- Unless it's caved in too.
- Well, yes.

13:10.623 --> 13:15.794
- You wanted to see me?
- Yes. You ready, Adam? Watch this.

13:16.670 --> 13:19.798
He can stand up all by himself.
Show Daddy.

13:20.007 --> 13:22.759
- All by himself. Stand up, Adam.
- That's my guy.

13:22.927 --> 13:24.010
Stand up.

13:24.512 --> 13:26.262
My son.

13:26.430 --> 13:30.767
Up, Adam, to the moon.

13:45.783 --> 13:47.575
Hey, boss.

13:47.743 --> 13:48.952
What do you make of this?

13:49.119 --> 13:51.621
- Damned if I know.
- Bet it's some kind of septic tank.

13:51.789 --> 13:53.957
Never seen a septic tank
that looked like that.

13:54.124 --> 13:57.210
Don't fool with it. If it is a septic tank,
I don't wanna open it.

13:57.378 --> 13:59.212
We'll just lay the foundation over it.

14:04.260 --> 14:09.097
"In Wonderland."

14:09.265 --> 14:13.852
I'd like to see the public school system
match that. I don't care how terrific it is.

14:14.019 --> 14:16.187
Don't you think
he's a little young for school?

14:16.355 --> 14:19.232
People have no idea
what the human mind is capable of.

14:19.400 --> 14:24.445
Look, Daddy. Alice went down a hole,
just like us.

14:24.613 --> 14:27.073
Will I ever get to go up on top?

14:27.241 --> 14:30.910
Yes, you certainly will,
and you'll find a nice girl...

14:31.078 --> 14:33.705
and rebuild America
just the way it used to be.

14:33.873 --> 14:37.834
Oh, Calvin. I'm not sure we should be
making promises that perhaps can't be kept.

14:38.002 --> 14:40.003
I'm convinced there'll be
other survivors.

14:40.170 --> 14:43.256
In fact, I'm guessing there's life
on the surface even now.

14:43.424 --> 14:47.510
Not life worth living, perhaps,
but believe me...

14:47.678 --> 14:49.637
something is moving around up there.

15:03.777 --> 15:06.446
I'm gonna need two more
banana splits and a Cherry Coke.

15:06.614 --> 15:08.031
You bet, Mom. Coming up.

15:08.198 --> 15:11.367
Oh, by the way, Mom, thanks for the job.

15:11.535 --> 15:13.870
- Buck-15 an hour.
- He's cute.

15:17.124 --> 15:18.833
Your husband is crazy.

15:20.210 --> 15:22.045
All right, what's the big news?

15:22.212 --> 15:26.299
- Ha-ha-ha. Ah.
- Oh, you're a riot.

15:26.467 --> 15:31.304
Oh, what a riot you are. Ha-ha-ha.

15:31.472 --> 15:34.265
- Watch this.
- Very funny. Ha-ha-ha!

15:34.433 --> 15:36.309
- Ha-ha-ha!
- You're a real riot.

15:36.477 --> 15:38.728
They're coming now to put you
on a stage.

15:38.938 --> 15:41.022
There's been complaints
about me on the bus.

15:41.190 --> 15:44.108
He's sending me
to the company psychiatrist.

15:44.276 --> 15:46.778
- Psychiatrist?
- Yeah, psychiatrist.

15:46.946 --> 15:50.365
- And that means I'm crazy.
- Oh, don't be silly, Ralph.

15:50.574 --> 15:53.826
Just sending you to a psychiatrist
doesn't mean you're crazy.

15:54.078 --> 15:56.120
Stick it. That's right.

15:56.288 --> 16:00.333
Hook off the jab. That's right.
Bob and weave. Bob and weave.

16:00.501 --> 16:01.834
Okay. Bob and weave.

16:02.002 --> 16:05.338
Excuse me, boys,
but I believe it's my turn now.

16:16.475 --> 16:19.978
Three, four, five...

16:20.145 --> 16:23.439
five, six, six, spin.

16:33.575 --> 16:36.661
- May I cut in?
- You certainly may.

16:36.912 --> 16:38.955
Thank you, sir.

17:14.907 --> 17:18.994
I miss those nice flower-power kids.
How about you?

17:19.829 --> 17:21.539
Ugh.

17:23.751 --> 17:25.209
I've heard people say

17:27.963 --> 17:30.423
What the hell kind of music is that?

17:31.925 --> 17:33.968
Oh, man.

17:34.136 --> 17:36.471
I'm not sure I like that.

17:37.639 --> 17:39.640
Change it.

17:39.808 --> 17:42.894
We've shared love and made love

17:44.063 --> 17:46.189
It's just not enough

17:46.356 --> 17:48.816
Oh, oh, babe

17:51.779 --> 17:54.989
My darling, I

17:55.157 --> 17:58.409
Can't get enough of your love, babe

17:59.369 --> 18:01.871
These are stock certificates.

18:02.039 --> 18:05.750
Your mom and I bought them for you.

18:05.918 --> 18:11.089
Of course, they're worthless now,
but at one time they were quite valuable.

18:11.298 --> 18:13.966
They're pretty. Could I have them?

18:14.176 --> 18:15.384
Heh. Sure.

18:15.552 --> 18:19.680
Now, let's move on to our French exam.

18:20.390 --> 18:22.975
Latin exam, Dad. It's Tuesday.

18:25.104 --> 18:29.690
Gosh, it is Tuesday.
Time flies, doesn't it?

18:43.914 --> 18:47.917
You have a wonderful sense
of humor, son, I must say.

18:48.460 --> 18:52.421
The acorn does not fall very far
from the tree.

18:53.006 --> 18:56.717
Oh, no! Agh! Oh, jeez. No.

18:56.885 --> 18:58.094
- I got you.
- I got...

18:58.262 --> 19:01.222
- Hi, hon.
- Hi.

19:06.353 --> 19:07.562
This is wonderful.

19:08.188 --> 19:12.650
It's my baseball card collection.
It's yours now.

19:13.777 --> 19:17.196
- What's baseball?
- It's a game, son.

19:17.364 --> 19:21.534
I can explain it pretty easily.
You see, there's a pitcher.

19:21.702 --> 19:23.619
Oh, like a painting?

19:23.996 --> 19:26.622
No. A pitcher.

19:26.790 --> 19:28.875
Like one of Mom's?

19:29.042 --> 19:33.129
No, there's a man who throws the ball
to a man who has a bat.

19:33.297 --> 19:36.674
- Oh, the nocturnal flying mammal?
- No.

20:00.616 --> 20:05.077
I'm selling this place.
I want out of this hellhole.

20:05.245 --> 20:07.997
Whoa. Uh....

20:08.165 --> 20:09.790
Could I, uh...?

20:09.958 --> 20:12.835
If you sell, uh....

20:13.462 --> 20:15.504
Me.... Could I, uh...?

20:15.672 --> 20:18.716
- Buy it from me?
- Yeah, yeah, that's it.

20:18.884 --> 20:22.845
- I'll give it to you, no money down.
- Cool.

20:23.555 --> 20:26.515
This neighborhood's going to hell,
anyway.

20:27.684 --> 20:31.646
At last! I am master of all I survey!

20:35.692 --> 20:36.776
No, no. Listen.

20:37.527 --> 20:40.154
I'm only gonna explain this
one more time.

20:40.322 --> 20:42.907
The runner on second goes to third.

20:43.075 --> 20:45.743
- It's... He's out there.
- Why?

20:45.911 --> 20:49.247
Because he's forced out.
It's... It's a force.

20:50.415 --> 20:54.585
- Then why go there?
- Because he must.

20:54.753 --> 20:57.922
- Calvin.
- Coming.

21:00.717 --> 21:01.884
Yes, dear?

21:02.052 --> 21:04.262
You get the presents,
I'll get the lights.

21:04.471 --> 21:05.972
You bet.

21:07.599 --> 21:11.852
Happy birthday to you

21:12.020 --> 21:15.856
And many more

21:16.024 --> 21:17.483
Ha!

21:18.235 --> 21:20.611
Thanks, Mom. Thank you, Dad.

21:20.862 --> 21:21.904
Blow out the candles.

21:22.072 --> 21:23.823
- Make a wish.
- Um....

21:29.871 --> 21:31.372
Here.

21:39.923 --> 21:42.925
Oh, boy, a jacket.

21:43.093 --> 21:46.095
- Your mom made that all by herself.
- No kidding?

21:46.263 --> 21:50.099
No kidding. Who else would have done it?

21:50.267 --> 21:52.310
I made these.

22:00.402 --> 22:02.695
Holy cow.

22:02.904 --> 22:04.780
What the heck are these?

22:04.990 --> 22:08.284
It's your roller skates, yup.
I redesigned them.

22:08.452 --> 22:11.287
These are really swell. I mean swell.

22:11.455 --> 22:13.122
Well, what did you wish for, son?

22:13.290 --> 22:16.167
- If he tells, it won't come true.
- That's a bunch of baloney.

22:16.335 --> 22:20.212
- My family never believed that.
- Well, we did, in my family.

22:20.422 --> 22:22.923
I wished that I could meet a girl.

22:24.134 --> 22:27.303
- Oh, well, a nice one?
- Yes, ma'am.

22:27.512 --> 22:31.974
- One that doesn't glow in the dark.
- Calvin Webber, what a thing to say.

22:32.184 --> 22:35.311
Well, we'll be going up in two years.
We'll know then.

22:35.479 --> 22:36.687
I'm very hopeful.

22:38.065 --> 22:39.231
Me too.

22:39.441 --> 22:40.649
- Elbows, son.
- Mm?

22:40.817 --> 22:43.444
Oh, I'm sorry, Mom.
What the heck am I thinking tonight?

22:43.612 --> 22:46.989
Well, you never know.
You might someday dine with the president.

22:47.157 --> 22:49.241
If we still have one. Ha, ha.

22:50.702 --> 22:54.288
You know, when we do go up,
I'm gonna miss this place.

22:57.542 --> 22:58.626
How about you, hon?

23:04.841 --> 23:07.343
Would you please excuse me?

23:07.511 --> 23:10.012
No, no, no, don't get up.

24:12.117 --> 24:15.911
- Should we say a prayer first?
- Just open the door.

24:30.760 --> 24:32.595
Long time.

24:35.474 --> 24:38.601
Well, it's dirty...

24:41.813 --> 24:44.106
but it seems to be okay.

24:47.569 --> 24:49.361
I know you're happy.

24:52.365 --> 24:54.658
Do we just go on up?

24:55.619 --> 24:56.785
No, son.

24:56.953 --> 25:00.331
Now is the time
we must be at our most cautious.

25:00.499 --> 25:03.876
- We wait for night.
- Oh, shit.

25:04.628 --> 25:06.128
Helen Thomas Webber...

25:06.338 --> 25:09.965
maybe we have been down here
a little too long.

25:10.759 --> 25:12.259
Pardon her French, son.

25:12.802 --> 25:14.303
"Shit" is French?

25:15.639 --> 25:16.889
Well, it's archaic French.

25:17.057 --> 25:22.186
It's a 16th-century colloquialism
meaning, roughly, "good."

25:22.395 --> 25:24.063
Your father's right.

25:24.231 --> 25:25.856
Well...

25:26.024 --> 25:27.358
shit.

25:29.861 --> 25:30.903
Ah.

25:42.707 --> 25:44.917
All of these things...

25:45.085 --> 25:50.548
Alcoholics Anonymous, Cocaine
Anonymous, uh, Heroin Anonymous...

25:50.715 --> 25:52.841
There's a Heroin Anonymous?

25:53.009 --> 25:56.011
Will you please shut up?

25:56.179 --> 25:57.555
Sorry, sorry.

25:57.722 --> 26:04.228
All of these things ask you to believe in
a power greater than yourself.

26:04.396 --> 26:08.607
Well, I have lifted my eyes skyward
a time or two...

26:08.775 --> 26:12.486
and I certainly have not seen
anything coming from up there.

26:12.654 --> 26:15.030
Except a goddamn airplane.

26:15.198 --> 26:18.033
Which I can't afford to get on.
Ha-ha-ha!

26:19.995 --> 26:22.538
Whoa, earthquake. Another earthquake.

26:22.706 --> 26:25.958
Let her come, let her come.
Let's get this over with.

26:36.052 --> 26:38.679
Oh, God. Oh, God.

26:40.223 --> 26:42.349
Oh, God.

26:42.517 --> 26:44.852
Oh, my God.

26:45.061 --> 26:46.854
Oh, God, save me.

26:49.733 --> 26:52.860
For I have seen the light.

27:01.995 --> 27:03.912
I come...

27:04.414 --> 27:06.081
in peace.

27:23.016 --> 27:26.894
Leave my elevator alone.

27:47.874 --> 27:51.168
What happened to my back yard?

28:29.124 --> 28:30.833
Got a light, honey?

28:31.584 --> 28:36.088
A light? Yes, I do have a light.

28:38.258 --> 28:40.342
Good. Thank you.

28:41.136 --> 28:45.639
- So you survived the blast.
- The blast? Ha, ha.

28:45.807 --> 28:47.766
Honey, I've survived a host of things.

28:47.934 --> 28:50.894
Like the song says,
a country boy can survive.

28:51.104 --> 28:52.938
Did you say you were a country boy?

28:53.148 --> 28:56.650
Cute little old man,
if you want a boy, I can be a boy...

28:56.818 --> 28:58.694
and if you want a girl, I can be a girl.

28:58.862 --> 29:00.320
I can be whatever you want me to be.

29:00.488 --> 29:01.989
- Really?
- Uh-huh.

29:02.198 --> 29:05.075
It's all yours
for the remarkably low price of $200.

29:05.285 --> 29:08.579
And if you act now, I may even
throw in some free lawn furniture.

29:08.747 --> 29:10.330
Now, how about that?

29:10.498 --> 29:12.833
No. Thanks.

29:13.001 --> 29:16.754
- Thank you. I have to go.
- Go.

29:16.921 --> 29:18.881
I have to go.

29:19.048 --> 29:21.550
Get out of here, you old drunk.

29:26.973 --> 29:29.892
Surprise. Bang! Ha-ha-ha.

29:30.059 --> 29:31.935
Oh!

29:36.524 --> 29:38.525
No!

29:41.321 --> 29:42.988
I'm gonna give it to you straight.

29:43.156 --> 29:45.157
There's no point
beating around the bush.

29:45.325 --> 29:46.408
There were survivors.

29:46.868 --> 29:51.997
Apparently, the fallout
has created a subspecies, mutants.

29:53.082 --> 29:55.042
Mutants?

29:55.210 --> 29:59.004
Not a pretty sight.
Some eat out of garbage cans, others...

29:59.172 --> 30:01.340
Cover your ears, son, and hum.

30:01.508 --> 30:04.092
I mean that literally.
I mean it right now.

30:06.012 --> 30:09.640
Others are multisexual.

30:09.849 --> 30:14.186
It seems they can be both masculine
and feminine simultaneously.

30:14.354 --> 30:15.771
- No.
- Yes.

30:15.939 --> 30:17.481
- I don't believe it.
- Believe it.

30:17.649 --> 30:20.567
He tried to sell me his body, Helen.

30:20.735 --> 30:24.029
They offer lawn furniture as a come-on.

30:26.866 --> 30:28.075
All right.

30:28.243 --> 30:30.077
They have done a lot of rebuilding...

30:30.286 --> 30:33.497
though society, at least
as we know it, has totally collapsed.

30:33.665 --> 30:37.000
People throw up in the streets.
Others point guns.

30:37.210 --> 30:39.878
There's something terribly wrong
with the automobiles.

30:40.046 --> 30:44.258
I can't tell you the rest, I just can't.
Maybe someday.

30:44.425 --> 30:47.094
- So, what do we do now?
- We stay down here.

30:47.262 --> 30:49.388
- We do?
- Yes. We'll make do.

30:49.556 --> 30:52.015
We have clothes,
we have running water from a well.

30:52.183 --> 30:54.810
I am convinced these mutants
will kill each other off...

30:54.978 --> 30:58.480
No, Calvin, we won't make do.
Not me, not Adam.

30:58.648 --> 30:59.982
We're going up.

31:00.149 --> 31:02.568
I don't care how horrible it is.
We deserve it.

31:02.735 --> 31:06.071
- I am the head of this household.
- I want him to at least see the sky.

31:06.239 --> 31:08.866
- We will.
- The ocean, a mountain.

31:09.033 --> 31:11.326
Do as I say!

31:19.210 --> 31:20.878
- Dad?
- Ugh!

31:21.045 --> 31:22.588
- Son...!
- Oh, Adam.

31:22.755 --> 31:24.965
Oh, my goodness.
Let's get him to the bedroom.

31:26.342 --> 31:29.261
He seems to be doing all right now.

31:29.470 --> 31:31.346
I don't know if he had a heart attack...

31:31.514 --> 31:35.017
or just a horrifying experience,
but we need supplies...

31:35.184 --> 31:37.269
and I've gotta stay with him.

31:37.437 --> 31:38.604
I'll go up.

31:39.397 --> 31:42.816
- I'm afraid you must.
- I'll be all right.

31:43.401 --> 31:45.569
My brave boy.

31:47.488 --> 31:51.241
Just act normal.
And if anyone asks, simply say:

31:51.409 --> 31:53.702
"I'm from out of town.
I'm here on business."

31:53.870 --> 31:56.163
- Here on business.
- Write that down.

31:56.664 --> 31:59.291
Now, I'm gonna give you
a shopping list and some money.

31:59.459 --> 32:02.044
We'll need enough to get
through the next year or two.

32:02.211 --> 32:05.631
You'll find these items at what used
to be called a grocery store...

32:05.798 --> 32:08.008
or a hardware store. Write that down.

32:08.176 --> 32:11.178
I don't know how far
you'll have to travel to find supplies...

32:11.346 --> 32:15.390
but if you can't get home by nightfall,
I want you to look for a Holiday Inn.

32:15.558 --> 32:20.479
It's a hotel. Write that down.
There might still be one left standing.

32:20.647 --> 32:22.105
Oh.

32:22.482 --> 32:25.692
- Well, let's get you packed.
- Right.

32:25.860 --> 32:27.736
Just hope this is still good up there.

32:27.904 --> 32:29.655
- Say, Mom?
- Yes, dear?

32:29.822 --> 32:31.531
I was wondering, um...

32:31.699 --> 32:34.660
you know, while I was up there
and all, I was thinking....

32:34.827 --> 32:38.288
Well, you know,
I was wondering if maybe I could, uh...

32:38.915 --> 32:40.749
meet a girl.

32:41.542 --> 32:45.587
I've been thinking about that a little.
Just these last 15 years or so.

32:45.797 --> 32:49.174
Oh, Adam, it would be wonderful
if you could meet a girl.

32:49.342 --> 32:52.219
One who's not a mutant
and hopefully comes from Pasadena.

32:52.387 --> 32:55.597
Nothing against Valley girls,
but in my day, anyhow...

32:55.765 --> 32:59.476
girls from Pasadena, I don't know,
just always seemed a little bit nicer.

32:59.644 --> 33:04.064
Oh, and, son, there's also something
called a liquor store.

33:04.232 --> 33:05.816
Write that down.

33:05.984 --> 33:07.859
Liquor store.

33:25.128 --> 33:26.795
Calvin?

33:32.969 --> 33:34.177
Son.

33:41.352 --> 33:42.728
Adam.

33:42.895 --> 33:44.146
Yes, Father?

33:44.313 --> 33:50.610
Don't forget:
Stay out of the adult bookstore.

33:51.195 --> 33:54.406
Adult bookstore. Why?

33:55.408 --> 33:59.578
Poison gas. Invisible.

34:01.205 --> 34:02.873
Don't forget.

34:03.041 --> 34:05.959
I promise. Is that all?

34:06.127 --> 34:07.669
Uh.

34:12.050 --> 34:13.216
One more thing.

34:15.553 --> 34:20.514
If you find a healthy young woman...

34:22.268 --> 34:24.226
bring her on down.

34:25.688 --> 34:27.063
Yes, sir.

34:27.648 --> 34:29.107
Uh.

34:49.587 --> 34:51.213
Are you all right?

34:51.380 --> 34:55.050
Yes, yes. Oh, Lord, yes.

34:55.217 --> 34:58.970
Are you the one who came last night
all in yellow?

34:59.180 --> 35:02.933
All in yellow? Oh, that was my father.

35:03.726 --> 35:05.769
Oh, of course. The father.

35:06.562 --> 35:11.233
Forgive me.
Can you forgive me for my wasted life?

35:11.442 --> 35:13.318
Everything has been so awful.

35:13.569 --> 35:16.404
I know, it has been terrible.

35:16.572 --> 35:18.740
But it's not your fault.

35:18.908 --> 35:22.327
And now that all the decay is over with,
things are going to get better.

35:22.954 --> 35:26.706
- You understand?
- Yes, yes.

35:28.793 --> 35:32.087
- Well, I have to go now.
- Of course, of course you do.

35:32.255 --> 35:36.216
- I'll stay here and pray.
- See, now, that's always a good idea.

35:36.425 --> 35:37.759
Yeah.

35:38.302 --> 35:39.761
How do I leave this place?

35:40.429 --> 35:42.139
Uh, the front door is open.

35:43.599 --> 35:45.475
Will you be back?

35:46.269 --> 35:47.602
I promise.

36:25.474 --> 36:26.892
What?

36:27.059 --> 36:28.685
What is it?

36:29.270 --> 36:30.312
The sky.

36:30.980 --> 36:34.774
- The sky? Where?
- Up there.

36:35.318 --> 36:37.819
- I don't see anything.
- Just look.

36:38.029 --> 36:39.988
What is it?

36:40.156 --> 36:42.908
He says he sees something.

36:46.662 --> 36:48.079
- What is it?
- The sky.

36:48.289 --> 36:49.331
I see it, Mommy.

36:49.498 --> 36:53.168
I have never in my life
seen anything like it before.

36:53.878 --> 36:56.004
Or like you.

37:02.887 --> 37:04.179
What are you looking at?

37:04.347 --> 37:07.682
Oh, my lucky stars, a Negro.

37:07.892 --> 37:10.101
- Say what?
- How do you do, ma'am?

37:10.311 --> 37:11.937
I do all right.

37:12.146 --> 37:16.233
- Ha, ha. Good.
- Okay?

37:18.069 --> 37:20.237
What is it? What do you see?

37:20.404 --> 37:23.114
Oh, we were just looking at the...

37:23.282 --> 37:24.824
- Oh, no!
- What?

37:24.992 --> 37:28.203
Poisonous gas! Run for your life!
Run! Run! Run for your life!

37:28.371 --> 37:31.539
Invisible poisonous gas!

37:35.962 --> 37:37.462
- You know...
- Aah!

37:39.924 --> 37:41.967
I just wanna say...

37:42.635 --> 37:44.886
I think he's gonna be fine.

37:45.721 --> 37:48.807
Thank you, Calvin. Thank you very much.

37:48.975 --> 37:50.267
He's smart.

37:50.434 --> 37:52.727
Yes, dear, I know.

37:53.271 --> 37:56.064
But he's still such a baby.

37:56.232 --> 37:58.900
He's a man.

37:59.068 --> 38:00.819
He's a baby man.

38:01.779 --> 38:06.574
I tried to give the driver this,
but he wouldn't take it.

38:07.660 --> 38:09.744
Seems kind of angry.

38:10.246 --> 38:11.705
Lot of people do.

38:11.872 --> 38:14.958
Oh, boy. Here we go.

38:15.126 --> 38:17.711
Hold on, everyone. Hold on.

38:17.878 --> 38:19.921
Wow. Ha-ha-ha.

38:20.089 --> 38:22.215
So this is public transportation.

38:22.383 --> 38:25.885
My father says it becomes more and
more important because of pollution...

38:26.053 --> 38:30.223
which is more and more carbon dioxide
and other hazardous gases in the air.

38:31.475 --> 38:33.268
Do you have a gun, by the way?

38:36.272 --> 38:39.399
Oh. Well, thank you
for not waving it around.

38:39.567 --> 38:42.277
And for not vomiting, for that matter.

38:42.486 --> 38:45.613
Say, do you know
where I could find a grocery store?

38:46.032 --> 38:47.073
I have to find that.

38:47.241 --> 38:49.451
That and a hardware store
and a liquor store...

38:49.618 --> 38:52.120
- ...and a standing Holiday Inn.
- Uh... Uh...

38:52.288 --> 38:55.123
- ...there's a grocery store up the street.
- Where? Where?

38:55.291 --> 38:56.750
- Up there.
- Oh, thank you.

38:56.917 --> 39:00.587
Driver, please stop the bus immediately.
I wish to get off.

39:00.796 --> 39:03.590
- Please stop the bus, sir.
- Stop the bus!

39:07.345 --> 39:09.804
- Paper or plastic?
- Paper, please.

39:10.014 --> 39:11.639
Do you have a club card?

39:13.267 --> 39:14.309
Here you go.

39:14.477 --> 39:16.728
I need a price check on Register 4...

39:16.896 --> 39:18.563
Diet Dr Pepper six-pack.

39:22.526 --> 39:24.444
- Ah-ha!
- Ha.

39:28.491 --> 39:31.826
A manager to the front,
check approval, Register 1.

39:32.036 --> 39:33.078
Can I help you?

39:33.245 --> 39:36.498
Oh, yes. Uh, I'd like to get
some all-beef patties.

39:36.665 --> 39:37.832
Fresh or frozen?

39:38.793 --> 39:43.088
Come on. Frozen. How much are they?

39:43.339 --> 39:46.007
Frozen they're 6.30 a dozen
in a 3-pound box.

39:46.175 --> 39:48.468
Twelve into 900 is 75.

39:48.677 --> 39:52.097
That's almost $500
just for the hamburger.

39:52.264 --> 39:54.849
My mother only gave me $3000
for everything.

39:55.059 --> 39:56.935
The yacht batteries, the pipe tobacco...

39:57.103 --> 40:00.271
the diesel oil, the bleach,
the floss, the birthday candles....

40:00.439 --> 40:03.525
You could get a meat order that big
delivered to your home.

40:03.692 --> 40:05.610
- Really?
- Sure.

40:05.820 --> 40:08.363
Oh, well, that's terrific. Heh.

40:09.323 --> 40:12.575
Except it just occurred to me
that I don't know where home is.

40:14.370 --> 40:15.995
I'm lost.

40:16.163 --> 40:18.331
- Do you know where I live?
- No.

40:18.541 --> 40:20.959
- Will you please excuse me?
- Gladly.

40:21.710 --> 40:23.294
Thank you.

40:47.736 --> 40:50.989
Driver, please stop the bus.

41:19.435 --> 41:21.769
- Hello.
- Hi.

41:21.937 --> 41:25.607
The name's Adam Webber,
and I see that you buy baseball cards.

41:25.774 --> 41:28.401
Although these are older
than the ones in the window...

41:28.569 --> 41:30.570
I was hoping
that you still might be interested.

41:30.738 --> 41:32.906
Uh... Oh, ahem.

41:33.073 --> 41:35.700
How much you want for this
Mickey Mantle rookie season?

41:35.868 --> 41:38.203
Well, I was hoping
to sell all of the cards.

41:38.412 --> 41:40.413
Really? No kidding?

41:40.581 --> 41:43.625
All I have are hundred-dollar bills.
I need something smaller.

41:43.792 --> 41:46.377
- You know, ones, tens, fives.
- I see what you mean.

41:46.545 --> 41:47.795
I'll tell you what.

41:47.963 --> 41:52.634
How about I give you $500
in small bills for the whole box?

41:54.303 --> 41:57.055
- That would be wonderful.
- Ah, shit.

41:59.141 --> 42:01.476
I'm working here, Evie-poo,
don't screw me up.

42:01.685 --> 42:04.896
Yeah, I can see you're working,
all right.

42:07.983 --> 42:09.400
Oh, you're French?

42:10.194 --> 42:14.155
No. I'm from out of town.
I'm here on business.

42:14.323 --> 42:16.616
Your business must not
be sports memorabilia...

42:16.784 --> 42:18.826
because this one Mantle card right here?

42:18.994 --> 42:22.163
Worth $6000 all by its itty-bitty self.

42:22.331 --> 42:25.291
- Get out of here.
- No, you get out of here.

42:25.501 --> 42:28.086
Terrific. You're fired,
you know that, huh?

42:28.295 --> 42:30.797
- I quit.
- No, no, no, I fired you.

42:31.006 --> 42:33.508
Just like the hair-salon guy
and the Chevy dealer.

42:33.759 --> 42:36.344
You know why
you can't keep a goddamn job?

42:36.512 --> 42:39.138
Because you can't keep
your goddamn mouth shut.

42:39.348 --> 42:41.349
Excuse me,
but I'd really appreciate it...

42:41.517 --> 42:44.102
if you wouldn't take
the Lord's name in vain again.

42:44.270 --> 42:46.271
You got a problem with that, partner?

42:46.480 --> 42:49.774
Yes, I have a big problem with that.

42:50.818 --> 42:53.528
Come on, Heathcliff. I'll walk you out.

42:54.655 --> 42:57.532
Yes, ma'am, but my name's Adam.

42:57.700 --> 43:00.535
Ha! Adam and Eve, the perfect match.

43:00.703 --> 43:03.037
I hope the two of you
will be very happy together.

43:03.247 --> 43:04.539
Mazel-fucking-tov.

43:04.748 --> 43:06.833
And don't come back, neither,
Miss Big-Shot.

43:07.001 --> 43:09.669
I'm serious,
you're finished in the hobby business.

43:09.878 --> 43:12.714
- So where are we going?
- We? I'm going home.

43:12.881 --> 43:15.842
Judging by that coat, you have to
get back to barber college.

43:16.010 --> 43:17.218
No, I'm lost.

43:17.386 --> 43:19.345
- Ugh. You're lost?
- Uh-huh.

43:19.513 --> 43:22.390
Say, did you just lose your job
back there because of me?

43:22.558 --> 43:25.393
Oh, forget about it.
I'm sick of working for that dickhead.

43:25.561 --> 43:26.728
- Dickhead?
- Yes.

43:26.895 --> 43:29.522
A walking penis
capable of intelligent speech.

43:29.732 --> 43:31.357
A dickhead.

43:31.900 --> 43:34.736
- What is wrong with you?
- I just had this mental picture...

43:34.903 --> 43:37.322
Here, help me pick these up.

43:37.489 --> 43:40.366
Oh, thank you.

43:41.201 --> 43:44.329
- Where are you parked?
- I came on a bus.

43:44.496 --> 43:45.913
Why does that not surprise me?

43:46.081 --> 43:48.082
I don't know,
why doesn't it surprise you?

43:48.334 --> 43:50.752
Well, I guess because
I'm a little psychic.

43:50.919 --> 43:54.088
- I have this thing.
- Oh, that's nice.

43:54.298 --> 43:58.092
Yeah. Let me guess something.
This is your first visit to la-la land.

43:58.302 --> 44:00.762
You're staying in Hollywood
because like an idiot...

44:00.929 --> 44:03.681
you thought that would be exciting.
Am I right so far?

44:03.849 --> 44:05.850
- So far.
- Yes, I'm right?

44:06.060 --> 44:07.393
- Right.
- I knew it.

44:07.561 --> 44:09.604
You get on a bus,
and before you know it...

44:09.772 --> 44:12.732
you're stuck in the
San Fernando Valley without a clue.

44:12.900 --> 44:14.942
- Correct again?
- Again.

44:15.110 --> 44:17.570
Where are you staying?

44:17.946 --> 44:19.238
The Holiday Inn.

44:19.406 --> 44:22.909
Whoa. Yes, yes, the Holiday Inn,
that's exactly right.

44:23.077 --> 44:26.454
See? I'm psychic. I mean,
not completely, but pretty much.

44:26.622 --> 44:30.208
- Pretty good, huh?
- No, it was amazing.

44:30.376 --> 44:31.751
Yeah, I know. Thanks.

44:31.919 --> 44:33.878
Anyhow, I'm gonna predict a bus for you.

44:34.046 --> 44:35.797
- You go down here...
- Do you own a car?

44:35.964 --> 44:38.716
Oh, no, sweetie.
Rule number one in North America:

44:38.884 --> 44:40.551
No strangers in the car.

44:40.719 --> 44:43.846
Well, if it'll make you feel any better,
I don't have a gun.

44:44.348 --> 44:45.390
Oh.

44:45.557 --> 44:48.893
Well, that changes everything.
Get away from me.

44:49.103 --> 44:51.104
Oh, no.
I'm sorry, I said something wrong.

44:51.271 --> 44:52.438
Please forgive me.

44:52.606 --> 44:54.565
- Get away from me.
- I'll make you a deal.

44:54.733 --> 44:57.860
I will give you a Rogers Hornsby
if you take me to the hotel.

45:00.406 --> 45:01.739
Rogers Hornsby?

45:02.324 --> 45:04.617
He's yours. I was holding him back.

45:04.827 --> 45:09.080
- Rogers Hornsby's worth like $4000.
- So what? I got two of them.

45:09.248 --> 45:14.419
And this many
Larry "Yogi" Berras and... And, uh....

45:14.628 --> 45:18.005
So for $4000, all I have to do
is drive you to your hotel?

45:18.173 --> 45:19.757
